bio.value:
USER is a Sound Creator from Vancouver Canada who has been releasing albums independently since the 90s. In 1996, USER's debut album, Semi-mental Journey, was the beginning of a large body of music USER has created 10 full-length and a bunch of singles with music videos.
‚ÄúI've made music in the underground clubs to the grassroots festivals, on large venue stages, down in greasy diners to the BC rocky beaches to beach hotels in Mexico and South America.
From the beginning when I created USER, it was from the shell of a grunge-rock outfit called Neptune Telescope, a local band from Vancouver that was making waves in the Indie scene in the mid 90s.
‚ÄúWe had lots of fun and the Vancouver music scene was on fire with lots of bands and with a smorgasbord of places to play like the Town Pump, Starfish Room, the Mighty Niagara, the brickyard, the Cobalt and the legendary Railway Club we had quite a draw.‚Äù
Then as with all rock bands, inner turmoil grew and the Band eventually ended. 
‚ÄúWe were in the middle of recording our first album at the historical Profile Studio with Brad McGivern and I took a Fear and Loathing month vacation thru the Midwest and came back and like that no band. I was left sitting on a large collection of recordings rather than let the songs collect dust in oblivion and the fact that it was 3 years' worth of recording I pushed forward Band Free.‚Äù
MID 90s
Finally, in June 1996 USER dropped the full-length Sem-Mental Journey.
‚ÄúHow did I choose, USER, well the engineer mastering guy Mark, had some picture wall hanging that had words user-friendly device, well the Tunes on the Disc were anything but ‚Äúfriendly‚Äù and it wasn‚Äôt about devices so I just stuck with the simple word then found some likely lads to jump aboard for live shows and USER was out the gate‚Äù
A video ensured. With some investment the Video was produced for the song ‚ÄúCyclops‚Äù with rotation on Much Music this really got the ball rolling, it garnered a lot of plays and interviews in the UK and North America, and Europe
The Late but Great 2010s
Never a single fan the writing was on the wall as digital streams began to herald the death of any real physical music products USER put out a rash of singles
In November 2018, the very 1st USER single ‚ÄúWelcome to the Real World‚Äù became available on all Music Platforms.
 "My studio is in a building that has a lot of late-night after-hour parties so sometime in the night, the walls would be shaking with heavy bass, it is like, cups would be breaking so rather than just take it, I would have everything set up keyboards and such and would just play along so that 30-second idea just grew and grew.‚Äù
For 2019 USER released 3 singles, the catchy ‚ÄúKitty Come On‚Äù, the Hard rock ‚ÄúAct of Nature‚Äù
And the prog doom epic ‚ÄúAftermath‚Äù
USER notes about the Single Kitty Come On, ‚ÄúI‚Äôve always been a cat lover, but I was so allergic. I finally got over my allergy enough to be able to pet a rescue cat from San Diego by the name of Azura and we have become good friends.
Also Digging thru the Vaults, I found some tunes I recorded way back, Act of Nature and Aftermath and dropping these early recordings was something I‚Äôve been achin to do‚Äù
Also 2019 ‚ÄúQuietly She Sips Her Blood‚Äù was finally released. An album of Rarities that USER had been harboring since the early 90s. 
‚ÄúI have always been about the songwriting so thru the years even if the bedroom tech was not as good as a big studio, I always took the time to make the recording as best as I could because I knew the future would have a solution for improving the sound‚Äù
Mostly Acoustic, this collection evolved at USER MEDIA studio in the heart of East Van.
 ‚ÄúI‚Äôve had this place for a long time over 20 years, at one point it was a very large hot spot in Vancouver for Musical artists to record but to this day there still lots of activity from DJ, painters craftsmen and musicians being creative here.‚Äù
THE 2020s LOCKDOWN FEVER
With Lockdown in the 2020s And Being a Night Owl, USER continues to pen more tunes than ever, but the vaults were still full of unfinished works.
The clock is always ticking and USER  in Lockdown fever came as a blessing and so more unreleased music is set forth upon the World ear including the Fall of Rome Rock Opus ‚Äú202Nine‚Äù and the haunting classical remastered ‚ÄúBulletproof‚Äù 
USER notes‚Äù202Nine was a tune I just never finished, then the bass line came to me in a semi-conscious state and I had to finish it as it seem fitting, Bulletproof was a 20-minute song of hidden tracks off of Semi-mental Journey I just cut it and remastered the piece and gave it the light it needed‚Äù
In the Winter of 2021, the pastoral acoustic Single is released ‚ÄúFalling into the Lie.‚Äù USER notes,‚Äù this gem was already cut and the tune only needed to be mastered. USER notes. ‚ÄúAfter a road trip to Seattle, I recorded this song after getting down with some Seattle record dudes there and realized the music biz is always as twisted as it always has been.‚Äù
In the spring of 2021, USER released ‚ÄúUS3RS‚Äù, Basically a best of Album of 21 songs. USER handpicks his favorite songs from his discography and clocking in at just over an hour this smorgasbord packs in a lot sounds and multi genre tunes that best describe 25 years of making music in modern times.
‚ÄúWith DAW and Mastering Software always improving I took the time to remaster some previous Tunes and although time-consuming it was well worth the endeavor as really improved my skill set.
IN Summer 2021 the rock ballad ABIGAIL STAR shoots to all corners of the world. 
ONCE again USER finishes a long-held recording that well took 15 years to see the public ear. USER describes the song as,
 ‚ÄúA fantasy-based recording in which describes elements of painting  I saw in the Smithsonian of a lover  who gets buried in the ground after the patriarchal ancient overlord sets up a plan to get rid of the daughter's lover. Meanwhile, the daughter turns into a fiery supernova and seeks revenge on the entire solar system.‚Äù
